    <h3>Tips and advice</h3>
    <p>Focus: <span class="definition-badge">Understanding features</span></p>
    <p>We knew that people weren’t fully aware of everything they could do on Bright Funds. Matching donations to fundraisers, setting up automatic donations, giving through payroll. These came up frequently through support conversations. </p>
    <p>At the same time, when people donate they’re not given advice on how to make the most of it. Say you have $1,000 of matching and are giving $50 per month. You’ll be leaving $400 of matching on the table. Figuring that out requires mental math. If I wanted to use all of my matching, I would need to do the monthly calculations myself.</p>
    <p>Helping someone understand what they could do would help them take full advantage of their various benefits. Helping them make better decisions would deliver higher value.</p>
    <p>We worked through these two types of tips. Educational tips (What can I do) and contextual advice (What do you suggest).</p>
    <p>I looked at a few visual treatments for the educational tips. We wanted them to be prominent, but not get in the way. For example, we knew that if we periodically displayed a modal with tips people would close it and not have a way to get back.</p>
    <p>Every user’s account has a home page with their giving and volunteering activity. I decided to take over the header of this page with the tips. By doing so, it was prominent (in the header of the first page someone sees when logging in), it didn’t get in the way, and it didn’t require new screen real estate.</p>

    </div>

